00:09:49,780 --> 00:09:52,140
then you can actually lose
far more than you invest

259
00:09:52,140 --> 00:09:53,050
by doing this.

260
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:55,780
Just imagine only investing
a thousand dollars

261
00:09:55,780 --> 00:09:56,750
of your own money,

262
00:09:56,750 --> 00:10:00,070
but waking up and being $7,000 in debt.

263
00:10:00,070 --> 00:10:01,970
Well, that's what you call a bad morning.

264
00:10:01,970 --> 00:10:04,850
This kind of situation
happens when you use leverage

265
00:10:04,850 --> 00:10:07,350
without fully understanding
the consequences.

266
00:10:07,350 --> 00:10:10,340
Many crypto brokers allow
you to trade on margin,

267
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:13,080
which simply means you're
able to multiply your money.

268
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:16,620
Some people are doing this
by a hundred X with Bitcoin.

269
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:17,453
When you do this,

270
00:10:17,453 --> 00:10:20,270
you maximize your profits
as you're investing more,

271
00:10:20,270 --> 00:10:22,300
but you'll also increase your risk,

272
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:24,390
as if the investment doesn't go well,

273
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:26,110
then you may be margin called

274
00:10:26,110 --> 00:10:28,940
and forced to sell all
your crypto at a loss.

275
00:10:28,940 --> 00:10:31,400
Although using leverage
is really tempting,

276
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,420
I always stay away from it personally.

277
00:10:33,420 --> 00:10:35,580
I know a lot of people
would disagree with me here.

278
00:10:35,580 --> 00:10:37,550
However, I'm a long-term investor,

279
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:40,480
and can't be sure what the
price of some cryptos will be

280
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,670
in the next day.

281
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:45,250
Therefore, I'm more interested
in the next 10 years.

282
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:47,090
That's of course, if I'm around that long.

283
00:10:47,090 --> 00:10:47,923
Because of this,

284
00:10:47,923 --> 00:10:50,590
I don't feel like using
margin is a smart move,

285
00:10:50,590 --> 00:10:52,610
even though I could
afford to pay things back

286
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:53,800
if it all went south.

287
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,980
If you still decide you
want to use leverage,

288
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:57,650
then I would just suggest making sure

289
00:10:57,650 --> 00:11:00,950
you fully understand the risk
involved before you dive in.

290
00:11:00,950 --> 00:11:04,320
Mistake number seven is not
storing your coins correctly.

291
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:08,940
Since 2011, over $1.65
billion worth of crypto

292
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:09,990
has been stolen,

293
00:11:09,990 --> 00:11:12,160
and the numbers are growing every year.

294
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:15,810
That amounts to a jaw-dropping
$12.6 billion loss

295
00:11:15,810 --> 00:11:18,050
when values are adjusted for inflation.

296
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:20,690
The nature of crypto makes
it extremely vulnerable

297
00:11:20,690 --> 00:11:23,610
to hackers, and if you don't
store it in a safe place,

298
00:11:23,610 --> 00:11:26,890
once your coins are stolen,
there is no way to recover them.

299
00:11:26,890 --> 00:11:28,330
You see the stories all the time

300
00:11:28,330 --> 00:11:30,630
